
Overview of noun ordeal

The noun ordeal has 2 senses (first 1 from tagged texts)
                                         
1. (3) ordeal -- (a severe or trying experience)
2. ordeal, trial by ordeal -- (a primitive method of determining a person's guilt or innocence by subjecting the accused person to dangerous or painful tests believed to be under divine control; escape was usually taken as a sign of innocence)
